      • Rdf2IfcConverter

        public Rdf2IfcConverter(IfcVersion ifcVersion,
                        boolean updateNS)
        Constructor
        Parameters:
        ifcVersion - IFC version for the conversion process
        updateNS - Set whether to update namespace for the ifcOWL ontology. Defaut value is false. If it is true, the converter will look up the namespace from the corresponding ifcOWL file in the resources folder and use it. Therefore the corresponding ifcOWL file must be updated before, otherwise it will still use the old namespace.

        public void convert(String inputUri,

                    org.apache.jena.riot.Lang lang,
                    String logFilePath)
             throws IOException
        Parameters:
        inputUri - File path of the input RDF file. RDF syntax is determined by the extension of input file, supported extensions are *.ttl (Turtle) and *.nt (N-Triple).
        outputFile - File path of the output IFC file.
        lang - RDF language, if it is null, it is determined by the extension of input file name.
        logFilePath - file path of the log file.
